Rating: 2
Now I think I understand why I'm the first to rate this recipe. If I'd done further research, I would have made the Mashed Sweet Potatoes with Maple Syrup, also on this site. As it was, the dish turned out very well, but only because I used one-third of the weight in sweet potatoes; of course, proportionaly less of the other ingredients, except for the maple syrup. Two tablespoons of maple syrup could hardly make a statement in 6 lbs. of sweet potatoes. I could barely get a taste of maple syrup in my 2 lbs. Having said all that, it still was a very tasty dish, and to the alternate recipe mentioned, I would add a touch of heavy cream as called for in the current recipe.